<HEADLINE>
DAVENPORT BEATS FRIEND
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE STEVENS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANHATTAN BEACH, Calif. _ Lindsay Davenport won her 10th
consecutive match on the Corel WTA tour when she beat Natasha
Zvereva 6-2, 6-3, in 55 minutes on Friday night in the
quarterfinals of the Acura Classic.
</P>
<P>
   The second-seeded Davenport faces fourth-seeded Monica Seles
tonight at 7 in the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
   Zvereva is Davenport's doubles partner and fellow Newport Beach
resident. The pairing presented a minor dilemma for Davenport.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was difficult to play her,'' Davenport said. ``But on the
other hand, it was the quarterfinals of a big tournament and we
both were looking to win.''
</P>
<P>
   Hingis' Nepal memories: When Martina Hingis visited Nepal in
late February to do charity work for the World Health Organization,
she learned something important, which she shared Friday. Expect
Hingis to continue to do charity work, but not in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
   ``You really have a lot of motivation to come home and practice
when you see that country,'' Hingis said. ``I will not go back
there.''
</P>
<P>
   Sanchez Vicario keying up: Third-seeded Aranxta Sanchez Vicario
advanced to the semifinals by beating Elena Tatarkova 6-3, 6-3.
Sanchez Vicario faces top-seeded Hingis today at noon.
</P>
<P>
   Sanchez Vicario says her main goal in the Acura Classic is to
prepare for the U.S. Open later this month. This tournament is her
first in two weeks. Any more of a hiatus for Sanchez would have
hurt.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's better to play as many tournaments as you can before the
Open,'' she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
