 Ditka Breaks a Promise  
 Buccaneers Practice Humility  
(bl) 
 By MIKE FREEMAN    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Ditka Breaks a Promise
</P>
<P>
   When New Orleans coach Mike Ditka made a vow last season to be a
calmer, gentler coach, few people in the NFL believed him. When he
went into orbit last week, getting into an expletive-filled
argument with linebacker Andre Royal, few people were surprised.
</P>
<P>
   Ditka cannot help himself. When Royal, who reported to camp
late, told Saints officials he had injured his right calf muscle,
Ditka did not buy it.
</P>
<P>
   ``Earn the money we're paying you,'' Ditka screamed at Royal.
``You don't fool anybody, least of all me.''
</P>
<P>
   Royal shouted obscenities back and said he has never faked an
injury. The next day, Royal was fined an undisclosed amount by
Ditka.
</P>
<P>
   Buccaneers Practice Humility
</P>
<P>
   The Tampa Bay Buccaneers might be the hot team in league and
news media circles when it comes to picking Super Bowl favorites,
but coach Tony Dungy is not going to let his players believe the
hype.
</P>
<P>
   Dungy called a team meeting and told his players not to get
cocky.
</P>
<P>
   Now, the only concern the team should have is with quarterback
Trent Dilfer.
</P>
<P>
   Dilfer has looked average at best during the preseason, and if
the Buccaneers are indeed going to get to the Super Bowl, he has to
play well. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
