<P>
   CLINTON-RECORD _ WASHINGTON _ Even if President Clinton did
something X-rated in private, goes the line spun out of the White
House, what counts is his public performance for the nation's
schools, families, economy and for its standing abroad. What
exactly has the Clinton administration accomplished, when measured
by its own goals? Certainly no president in memory, and probably
ever, has offered a higher stack of promises. With each campaign
and State of the Union address, Clinton has spread out scores of
new initiatives and proposals, from the minuscule to the expansive,
like so many hoagies and puff pastries on a vast smorgasbord. And
six years into his presidency, a few have been delivered, some have
been sent back to the kitchen by the Republican Congress, and many
others some seem a bit, well, moldy. (Malone, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moved Monday in (k) commentary.
