granite from the old Pennsylvania Station at the New Jersey
Meadowlands, in East Rutherford, N.J. The Pennsylvania Station
Redevelopment Corporation, a state agency, hopes to use
architectural remnants from the long-lost building as decorative
elements in a new passenger concourse and ticketing hall it is
planning in Manhattan. (Nancy Siesel//New York Times Photo)
