   Today, when the Chicago Cubs rookie takes the mound in the
Astrodome for his first professional start in his home state, he
will be trying to halt a flameout.
</P>
<P>
   Though Wood has an 11-6 record and 193 strikeouts in 138 innings
in his rookie season, he has hit a wall of late. In his last two
starts, Wood has lasted only 10 innings and allowed 14 hits and 12
runs.
</P>
<P>
   Those starts came after Cubs manager Jim Riggleman mentioned he
thought that Wood might be suffering a dead arm, a malady that
