berth.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've got 10 starts left this year. Last year at this time, I
might have two or three left,'' said Wood. ``So we're cutting back
a little bit (on throwing) in between starts, taking it a little
easy and see how that works. We're seeing how I recover from the
start before and see how my arm reacts.
</P>
<P>
   ``If we're up four, five runs going into the seventh, I might
not go out there this late in the season. In the home stretch, I
want to be able to reach back. I think it's important to do it
(taper off) now rather than not have enough left in the stretch. I
want to be able to turn it up a notch a little later on. Every game
is going to count. I'd rather miss an inning or two now and maybe
even a start rather than not have enough left at the end of the
season.''
</P>
