   After Wood was hit hard for the second straight time last week
at San Francisco, Giants second baseman Jeff Kent explained what he
thought was happening to Wood.
</P>
<P>
   ``If he's not throwing with Nolan Ryan speed, you'll be able to
hit the fastball,'' said Kent, who hit a home run off Wood. ``I'd
hate to see Kerry Wood on a good day because it'd be a struggle to
hit that slider.
</P>
<P>
   ``He hung a lot of pitches and wasn't throwing them consistently
for strikes, so we were able to sit on fastballs. It showed me he's
tired.''
</P>
